programme.title: Tipping Point
programme.desc: Ben Shephard hosts the quiz show in which contestants answer questions to win turns on an arcade-style machine. Dropping tokens down a choice of four chutes, they hope to knock piles of them off a moving shelf - and the more they collect, the greater the prize fund. The player who has won the least amount is then eliminated, and the last one standing competes for a £10,000 jackpot.(n)

programme.title: Tipping Point
programme.desc: Game show, hosted by Ben Shephard, in which contestants answer questions to win turns on an arcade-style machine. Dropping tokens down a choice of four chutes, they hope to knock piles of them off a moving shelf - and the more they collect, the greater the prize fund. programme.title: The Restaurant
programme.desc: Marie Cassidy & Marco Pierre White Pathologist Marie Cassidy is whisked off to Wineport Lodge in Glasson, Co Westmeath, where she is challenged to step into the role of chef for the evening, preparing a top-quality three-course meal for guest critic Marco Pierre White. Marie must also select two value-for-money wines to adequately complement her dishes and ensure she receives positive feedback.(n)

programme.title: Celebrity Catchphrase
programme.desc: Stephen Mulhern hosts a celebrity edition of the game show, asking contestants Chris Hoy, Martine McCutcheon and Faye Tozer to 'see it and say it' as they try to guess the familiar phrases hidden in animated clues. After the first elimination, the two remaining players battle to reach the Super Catchphrase round, where one of them could win £50,000 for their chosen charity.(n)

programme.title: River Monsters
programme.desc: Flesh Ripper Extreme angler Jeremy Wade visits New Zealand in search of a mysterious 8ft creature as described more than 200 years ago by a famous explorer. In trying to discover whether he is dealing simply with a legend or a real flesh-and-blood monster that has allegedly attacked divers and even seized a child, he finds the remote rivers and deep lakes would provide an ideal refuge for the predator.(n)

programme.title: Sport Stories
programme.desc: Sport Stories: Kenneth Egan An interview with the Olympic boxing silver medallist, who discusses his journey to the top of the amateur boxing world and his hidden struggles with addiction.(n)

programme.title: Celebrity Supermarket Sweep
programme.desc: Trolley-dashing in Rylan Clark-Neal's supermarket for the chance to win £10,000 for charity are Loose Women's Andrea McLean and Nadia Sawalha, football legends Harry Redknapp and Paul Merson, and actor friends Rita Simons and Chizzy Akudolu.(n)

programme.title: Alan Carr's Epic Gameshow
programme.desc: Strike It Lucky The comedian hosts a revival of classic game show Strike It Lucky. Three pairs of players will be choosing the top, middle or bottom as they navigate their way across a sea of screens, trying not to let their greed stop them banking too many prizes, and avoiding the infamous hotspots. One lucky pair will reach the endgame, where they stand to win a mountain of prizes and a luxury holiday to Las Vegas.(n)

programme.title: Models: Street to Catwalk
programme.desc: Cutting-edge modelling agency Nemesis offers Manchester's most underprivileged teens a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.(n)

programme.title: Love Island USA

programme.title: Shayne Ward: That's My Noughties
programme.desc: Shayne Ward takes us down memory lane with a nostalgic noughties playlist! You'll know all the words to Clocks, Mercy, Rock DJ and the rest.(n)

programme.title: Becky Hill's Dance Masterclass
programme.desc: From house to drum and bass, disco to EDM, Becky Hill opens the doors to her classroom, as she shares her knowledge and passion for the genre of dance.(n)

programme.title: Hits Don't Lie: RnB Anthems
programme.desc: From anthemic slow jams to throwback classics, Swarzy brings you an ultimate assembling of tracks that forged the direction and influenced the sound of R&B as we know it.(n)

programme.title: Fresh for 2022
programme.desc: Abbie McCarthy brings you the freshest new artists who we think are going to be BIG this year! Featuring Thomas Headon, Amaria BB, Lola Young & ArrDee.(n)

programme.title: Don't Tell the Bride
programme.desc: Charles and Lauren A 30-year-old Newcastle man hopes to give his 26-year-old art-teacher fiancee the wedding of her dreams. The couple have been inseparable since they met five years ago while working behind a bar, but the groom's love of science fiction is at odds with the bride's sophisticated tastes.(n)

programme.title: Don't Tell the Bride
programme.desc: Anna and Sian Anna, a 31-year-old support worker from Liverpool hopes to give her fiancee Sian the ceremony of her dreams. However, she struggles to set aside her tomboy tendencies and adapt to the feminine world of wedding planning, and best woman Jade threatens to be more of a hindrance than a help.(n)

programme.title: The Goldbergs
programme.desc: Baré After Barry starts checking out the best medical schools, Lainey reveals she has won a scholarship to art college. Erica and Adam start to suspect that Murray loves the family dog Lucky more than them.(n)

programme.title: The Goldbergs
programme.desc: A Night to Remember Barry plans big romantic gestures for Lainey on high school prom night, while Erica and Geoff try to attend the event together, but things don't go as planned. Adam is thrilled when a nerdy but cute girl asks him out, but is horrified when Beverly gets involved.(n)

programme.title: The Goldbergs
programme.desc: The Dynamic Duo Barry attempts to drive a wedge between Adam and Pops when they debate the merits of a recently released Batman movie. Erica deliberately makes a mess of her interview at one university so that she will only receive an offer from her first choice of college, but her plan goes badly awry. Comedy, starring Wendi McLendon-Covey, Sean Giambrone and Hayley Orrantia.(n)

programme.title: The Goldbergs
programme.desc: Fonzie Scheme Murray is honoured as one of the area's top businessmen, Beverly's attempt to help her husband find a hobby backfires, and Erica comes to the rescue when Barry's scheme to steal golf carts goes awry.(n)

programme.title: The Goldbergs
programme.desc: The Day After The Day After A scary TV movie motivates Barry to beg his father to build an underground bunker for the family, but Murray isn't easily persuaded. Erica and Adam go over the top with lavish Mother's Day gifts for Beverly before bringing important requests to her. Comedy, starring Wendi McLendon-Covey and Jeff Garlin.(n)

programme.title: The Goldbergs
programme.desc: Jedi Master Adam Skywalker As the academic year comes to a close, Barry and Erica wonder how they will appear in the school yearbook and pressure Adam, who is on the team producing it, to see the rough layout before it goes to print. Murray is annoyed when Marvin pays a visit to ask for money. Comedy, starring Wendi McLendon-Covey and Jeff Garlin.(n)

programme.title: The Goldbergs
programme.desc: Graduation Day Erica cannot wait to get out of the house as Graduation Day approaches - until it dawns on her how much her mother's affection means to her. Barry's plans for a summer with Lainey turn to dust, while Dana makes an unexpected visit. Comedy, starring Wendi McLendon-Covey and Hayley Orrantia.(n)

programme.title: The Goldbergs
programme.desc: Weird Science Beverly and Murray help Erica move into her college dormitory, where her room-mate is also named Erica, but Beverly has a hard time saying goodbye to her daughter. Now that Lainey has gone to college, Adam tries to find the perfect girlfriend for Barry, even pretending to build one, as in the film Weird Science.(n)

programme.title: The Goldbergs
programme.desc: Hogan Is My Grandfather Adam has to tackle a school project on the Second World War, so decides to make a film featuring his grandfather. However, Pops takes matters into his own hands when Adam finds all his war stories mundane. Erica fails to cope with her own cooking and laundry at college and returns home to confront Beverly for over-mothering her, but Murray insists that Beverly starts to teach Erica and Barry basic life skills.(n)

programme.title: The Goldbergs
programme.desc: Goldberg on the Goldbergs Beverly intervenes when she finds out that Coach Mellor has a strained relationship with his brother, Coach Nick, but when the two men face off in the gym, Adam and Barry join in. Meanwhile, Geoff and Erica struggle with their long-distance relationship.(n)

programme.title: The IT Crowd
programme.desc: Return of the Golden Child Denholm's death spells trouble for Jen and Roy - until support appears in the form of a mysterious stranger. Elsewhere, Moss is intrigued by a website that uses people's personal details to calculate when they will die. Comedy, starring Chris O'Dowd.(n)

programme.title: Rick and Morty
programme.desc: Lawnmower Dog Rick helps Jerry out with the family dog Snuffles by creating a device to make him more intelligent, but things go awry. Rick and Morty also invade the dreams of Morty's maths teacher Mr Goldenfold in an effort to raise Morty's grades. Rob Paulsen and Jess Harnell guest star.(n)

programme.title: Rick and Morty

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: 2017: Algarve, Portugal Jasmine Harman shows London-based Sri Lankan couple Kulan and Kamala five properties for their budget of £200,000 in Portugal's Algarve region. However, it remains to be seen which property has the most 'wow' factor to become the accountants' dream holiday home.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: 2017: Eastern Andalucía, Spain Childhood sweethearts Thomas and Doreen from Sunderland have been dreaming of owning a holiday home in Spain since their first anniversary there 39 years ago. Scarlette Douglas searches far and wide to find them the perfect property in eastern Andalucía for their £55,000 budget. But will it be a modern apartment near the sea or a traditional cave house in the countryside that wins their hearts?(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: 2018: Barbados Mark and Maggie have been together for 35 years and are looking for a holiday home in Barbados, where they can escape British winters and make the most of the tropical climate. With a budget of £350,000, Jasmine Harman uses her extensive knowledge of the island to find the best properties for the pair to choose between.(n)

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces
programme.desc: Architect George Clarke follows the fortunes of a 21-year-old fitness fanatic converting a 1920s railway carriage into a fully equipped luxury gym and sauna and the man going potty over converting a Victorian ladies loo into a romantic getaway. The presenter also visits a magnificent French chateau in the heart of Buckinghamshire. Together with master craftsman Will Hardie, George formulates an ingenious space-saving plan to convert a studio flat prototype into a magical secret garden.(n)

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces
programme.desc: Sewage Works, Chapel & Japan Architect George Clarke meets an old friend in Norfolk who is planning to turn an old sewage works into a unique chill-out space for his family, complete with a self-supporting dome roof and a circular carp pond. A Midlands father and daughter work together on salvaging a dilapidated childhood treehouse with a budget of just of £300, George and Will find unusual inspiration as they continue building their own treehouse, and in Japan, George visits a breath-taking chapel made of intertwining concrete ribbons.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: 2017: Almeria, Spain After a road trip along the Spanish coastal region of Almeria, Frans and Julie Mampaeij from Berkshire completely fell in love with this part of the country. Now they want to seize the day and buy a holiday home here. With a cash budget of £90,000, Scarlette Douglas shows them five properties for them to choose between.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: 2018: Costa del Sol Ian Steadman and Maria Callaghan want to buy their first property together in Estepona, their favourite location on Spain's Costa del Sol. Jasmine Harman searches every nook and cranny of the local market seeking a suitable property for £150,000 or less.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun

programme.title: Columbo
programme.desc: Short Fuse The son of a chemical company's founder is blackmailed by his uncle, who wants to force him into selling the business. The cunning heir responds by murdering his relative with a box of exploding cigars, but finds himself facing the dishevelled detective, who is convinced the resulting fatal detonation was no accident. Crime drama, starring Peter Falk, Roddy McDowall and Ida Lupino.(n)

programme.title: Columbo
programme.desc: Old Fashioned Murder A woman who has devoted her life to running her family's museum is outraged when her brother decides to sell it. Knowing of someone with criminal connections, she arranges to have her brother killed. However, just when she starts to think she has got away with it, a certain shabby sleuth is assigned to the case. Crime drama, with Peter Falk, Joyce Van Patten, Celeste Holm and Tim O'Connor.(n)

programme.title: Columbo
programme.desc: The Greenhouse Jungle A penniless rare-plant collector, desperate for funds to support his expensive hobby, fakes his nephew's kidnapping to get his hands on a trust fund. However, the supposed victim turns up dead, prompting Columbo to take action to unmask the killer. Detective drama, starring Peter Falk, Bradford Dillman and Ray Milland.(n)

programme.title: Columbo
programme.desc: The Most Crucial Game The owner of an American football team is found dead in a swimming pool, and his drowning is regarded as an accident. The down-at-heel detective is convinced that foul play was involved and sets out to prove his case - but his chief suspect has a cast-iron alibi that places him miles away from the scene of the crime. Detective drama, starring Peter Falk and Robert Culp.(n)

programme.title: Columbo
programme.desc: Make Me a Perfect Murder A TV executive's assistant responds to being denied a promotion by killing her boss, then uses her years of experience working on detective shows to create the perfect cover-up. But she reckons without the intervention of Columbo, who begins laying his trap for her while also nursing a neck injury. Crime drama, starring Peter Falk and Trish Van Devere.(n)

programme.title: Columbo
programme.desc: Mind Over Mayhem A scientist is overjoyed when his son follows in his footsteps, receiving widespread acclaim for a revolutionary new theory. When a fellow boffin produces evidence of plagiarism, the ruthless father resorts to murder to save his son from a scandal. But he reckons without the dishevelled detective, who sees through his efforts to make the killing look like the work of burglars. Crime drama, with Peter Falk, Jose Ferrer and Lew Ayres.(n)

programme.title: Columbo
programme.desc: Ransom for a Dead Man A devious lawyer hatches the perfect murder plot - she kills her husband, tells the police he has been kidnapped and leaves the body at the ransom drop, making it look like the criminals who abducted him finished him off. However, the crumpled cop sees through her ruse and begins picking apart her story in his inimitable manner. Detective drama, starring Peter Falk, Lee Grant and Patricia Mattick.(n)

programme.title: Law & Order: Special Victims Unit
programme.desc: Philadelphia Benson locates her long-lost brother's house in New Jersey, only to discover he is suspected of stalking three women and breaking into their homes. She also investigates a serial rapist attacking men in Central Park, but her inquiries are hampered by the latest victim's refusal to testify for fear of his fiancee's reaction. Crime drama, starring Mariska Hargitay.(n)

programme.title: Law & Order: Special Victims Unit
programme.desc: Sin The discovery of a murdered man in a graveyard leads Munch to discover he was a rent boy, who had recently made calls to a church known for its notorious anti-gay beliefs. The institution's founder confesses to the crime as the evidence mounts against him, but the detectives suspect he is taking the blame for someone else. Crime drama, starring Richard Belzer.(n)

programme.title: Law & Order: Special Victims Unit
programme.desc: Uncle Stabler and Beck arrest a homeless man on suspicion of the rape and murder of a woman and her 10-year-old daughter - only to find he is actually Munch's estranged uncle Andrew . As the case proceeds, a new suspect is identified, but the evidence against him is thrown out in court - and events build to a tragic conclusion. Drama, starring Christopher Meloni and Connie Nielsen.(n)

programme.title: Teleshopping
programme.desc: TJC A chance to buy goods from the comfort of home.(n)

programme.title: Criminals: Caught on Camera
programme.desc: Journalist Nick Wallis joins police forces around the nation to discover how CCTV and technological advances are helping to bring criminals to justice. The programme reveals how essential surveillance cameras have become in the fight against crime and features footage of people caught red-handed.(n)
